Three of my friends and I went there because I was craving BBQ and throughout the entire time we were there, I ordered and spoke with the staff in Chinese even though my friends and I speak English. The staff were not very friendly, one of them rolled her eyes at me when I asked her to wait just a second while ordering to make sure the food is what everyone wants. However, even after all that hostility, I still decided to leave a generous tip at the table upon leaving despite my boyfriend's discouragement. As we stood up to leave, an older looking waitress (possibly the owner) intercepted me and loudly announced, "you know you need to give tip right?!" in a nasty tone without even looking at the big tip I had left at the table. First of all, NO establishment should say such a thing to customers let alone in front of many other paying customers. It's rude beyond belief. And second, it's really shocking how tolerant I was of this unacceptable attitude from the minute we sat down to the second we stood up. My friends were baffled. The staff there are a disgrace to not only them as a restaurant business, but also us as Chinese Americans. The food was decent but the whole experience is what truly matters. My friends and I came to have a good time but what we got instead was a bad impression. Would definitely not recommend for dinner with friends. Maybe try to go alone and hope they will give you better treatment than what they gave us.
